sql:
SELECT type_name
FROM vehicle_types
WHERE type_id = 1;

SELECT COUNT(association_id) 
FROM vehicle_type_associations 
WHERE type_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- 'Manual transmission' refers to a type of vehicle transmission where the driver controls the gear shifts manually;
- 'Regular fuel' is a type of gasoline with a standard octane rating;
- 'Miles per gallon (mpg)' is a measure of fuel efficiency, indicating how many miles a vehicle can travel on one gallon of fuel.

- 'Top 5 brands' are determined by the number of vehicles each brand produces;
- 'Fuel efficiency' is measured by miles per gallon (MPG);
- 'Most recent models' refers to the latest model years.

- "Outperform their type's average fuel efficiency" means the vehicle's MPG is greater than the average MPG for vehicles of the same type;
- "Fall short of the overall fleet's average" means the vehicle's MPG is less than the average MPG of all vehicles in the fleet;
- "Fueled by premium options" implies the vehicle uses fuel with an octane rating higher than the average octane rating of all fuel types;
- "Elite athletes" is a metaphor for vehicles that perform better than their peers;
- "League's champions" is a metaphor for the top-performing vehicles in the overall fleet.

- "Diesel-powered vehicle" refers to a vehicle that uses diesel fuel;
- "Efficiency" in this context is measured by the average miles per gallon (mpg);
- "Top result" means the vehicle with the highest average mpg among those that meet the criteria.

- "Most fuel-efficient types of vehicles" refers to those with the highest average miles per gallon (MPG);
- "From the East" refers to vehicles from Asian countries;
- "Blossomed since 2010" means manufactured after 2010;
- "Stand out in the top 5 of their year" means ranked within the top 5 by average MPG within the same model year;
- "Combined fuel efficiency that surpasses a marathon runner’s endurance of 500 miles" means the total MPG for all vehicles of that type in the same model year is greater than 500.

- "Outshines its peers" refers to vehicles having a higher fuel efficiency (MPG) compared to other vehicles of the same type;
- "Top 10 within its category" means the vehicle is among the top 10 in terms of fuel efficiency (MPG) when compared to other vehicles of the same type;
- "Surpassing the average fuel efficiency of its type" means the vehicle’s MPG is greater than the average MPG for its vehicle type.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(vehicle_id)
FROM transmission_type_associations
WHERE transmission_id = 0;

SELECT type_name, AVG(average_mpg) AS avg_mpg
FROM vehicle_types
GROUP BY type_name;

external_knowledge:
